<article>
    <h1>5&#xD;&#xA;RECORD OF YOUTH (2020)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201113/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-13"><time>2020-11-13</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Park Bo-gum, Byeon Woo-seok and Park So-dam (of last year’s Par­a­site movie fame) fea­ture in this se­ries about hip 20some­things try­ing to make it big in the fash­ion industry.</p>
    <p>With the lads play­ing mod­els and Park So-dam a make-up artist, the South Korean stars pro­vide some of the show’s trendi­est looks.</p>
    <p>It is a rare pro­duc­tion where the men’s looks out­shine the ladies’.</p>
    <p>Pick up style in­spi­ra­tion from the two male leads, who tog­gle be­tween model off-duty streetwear and sharply tai­lored suits. They stay cosy in preppy knitwear from Polo Ralph Lau­ren and hood­ies lay­ered un­der de­signer blaz­ers.</p>
    <p>The show also trend-spots mini bags, slung ef­fort­lessly over both the guys and gals.</p>
    <p>Watch it on: Net­flix</p>

